  "legacy": {
    "summary": "Season 1 established the foundation with 24 new players and hidden immunity idols. Lindsay's social mastery defeated Alejandro's strategic gameplay in a classic 5-4 vote. The season featured unprecedented chaos: 2 ties, multiple revotes, a rock draw, and a medevac.",
    "franchiseRecords": [
      "\ud83d\udc51 Most Wins: Lindsay (1)",
      "\ud83c\udfaf Biggest Target: Beth (22 votes against)",
      "\ud83d\udcaa Best Challenge Player: Bridgette (5 challenge wins)",
      "\ud83e\udde0 Best Strategic Player: Alejandro",
      "\ud83d\udee1\ufe0f Best Social Game: Lindsay (1 vote against)",
      "\ud83e\udea8 Most Chaotic Season: Season 1 (2 ties, revotes, rocks, medevac)"
    ],
    "memorableMoments": [
      "Justin eliminated with an idol in his pocket \u2014 the first of many wasted shields this season.",
      "Duncan transfers the Screaming Gophers Limited Idol to Gwen, then Gwen passes it to Alejandro \u2014 one player quietly accumulates two idols.",
      "The Kidnapping Twist: the Screaming Gophers exile Noah to the opposing tribe, fracturing his alliance and reshaping the merge.",
      "Heather plays the Campers Idol on Bridgette \u2014 not to save her, but to keep Trent emotionally exposed. Pure psychological warfare.",
      "Sadie eliminated by rock draw at the F6 tie without receiving a single vote \u2014 she refused to blink and the game broke her.",
      "Owen medically evacuated at Final 6, the only player targeted unanimously who never had to face a vote.",
      "Alejandro controls two hidden idols simultaneously for three consecutive tribals \u2014 the most individual power any player has held in the franchise.",
      "Lindsay wins 5-4 over Alejandro \u2014 the jury rewards kindness that never cracked over calculated dominance."
    ]
  }
